# 🛠️ VPC Demo: 2-Tier Application in Private Subnets

This project demonstrates how to set up a **2-tier architecture** using **AWS VPC**, where both the application and database layers are hosted in **private subnets**. The setup follows best practices by using a **NAT Gateway** for outbound internet access.

---

## 📺 Video Walkthrough

Watch the full step-by-step tutorial here:  
[![YouTube Video](https://img.shields.io/badge/Watch-YouTube-red?logo=youtube)](https://youtu.be/FZPTL_kNvXc)

---

## 📷 Architecture Diagram

![VPC Private Subnets](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/images/vpc/latest/userguide/images/vpc-example-private-subnets.png)

---

## 🌐 Key Features

- Custom **VPC** with private and public subnets
- **NAT Gateway** for private subnet internet access
- **App Tier** and **DB Tier** hosted in separate private subnets
- Suitable for secure production environments

---

## 🚀 Technologies Used

- AWS VPC
- Subnetting (Private/Public)
- NAT Gateway
- EC2 Instances (App + DB)
- Internet Gateway (for NAT access)

